    <!--about mental health-->
    <h1 style="color: #6495ED;
        text-align: center;font-weight: bold">
        Understand

    </h1>
    <br />
    <div>
        <p style="font-size:20px; width: 950px; display: block; margin: 0 auto">
            Mental health can affect how you feel, think, behave and relate to others.
            It covers a spectrum of disorders that affect your mood, thinking and behaviours.
            Depression and anxiety are commonly face by people from time to time and can become a concern when ongoing signs and symptons cause frequent stress and affect your ability to function.
            In most cases, symptons can be managed with a combination of medications and therapy.
        </p>
        <br />
        <p style="font-size:20px; width: 950px; display: block; margin: 0 auto">
            Read below by going to each card to know more about mental health.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-5" style="background-image: url(https://i.loli.net/2020/09/14/thMiQjyWz5Lurpw.jpg)">
        <h2 style="text-align:center;line-height:250px;color:white;font-size:35px">Causes</h2>
        <div class="overlay">
            <div class="text">

                Mental illnesses, in general, are thought to be caused by a variety of genetic and environmental factors:
                <br />• Inherited traits
                <br />• Environmental exposures before birth
                <br />• Brain chemistry

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-5" style=" background-image: url(https://i.loli.net/2020/09/14/oNdI259OLwilB1c.jpg)">
        <h2 style="text-align:center;line-height:250px;color:white;font-size:35px">Risks</h2>
        <div class="overlay">
            <div class="text">
                Certain factors may increase your risk of developing a mental illness, including:
                <br />• A history of mental illness in a blood relative
                <br />• Stressful life situations
                <br />• An ongoing (chronic) medical condition
                <br />• Use of alcohol or recreational drugs
                <br />• A childhood history of abuse or neglect
                <br />• Few friends or few healthy relationships
                <br />• A previous mental illness
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div>
        <div class="col-md-5" style="        background-image: url(https://i.loli.net/2020/09/14/YQxdgmeyfLWGZnM.jpg)">
            <h2 style="text-align:center;line-height:250px;color:white;font-size:35px">Preventation</h2>
            <div class="overlay">
                <div class="text">
                    There's no sure way to prevent mental illness:
                    <br />• Pay attention to warning signs
                    <br />• Get routine medical care
                    <br />• Get help when you need it
                    <br />• Take good care of yourself
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-5" style="        background-image: url(https://i.loli.net/2020/09/14/t2v8pLSRCTgIAud.jpg)">
            <h2 style="text-align:center;line-height:250px;color:white;font-size:35px">See Doctor</h2>
            <div class="overlay">
                <div class="text">
                    If you have any signs or symptoms of a mental illness, see your primary care provider or a mental health professional.
                    <br />Lifeline ☎️ 22 131114
                    <br />Contact lifeline for support if you are experiencing a personal crisis or have suicidal thoughts. you can call them 24 hours a day, 7 days a week from anywhere in australia.

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>


